Applying to ACL Year-Long Mentorship

Apply to be a Mentee

You can apply as a mentee if you are a junior researcher in NLP and needs help with career choices, starting to do NLP research, and so on. To check whether you are eligible, please scroll down to see the Eligibility Requirements.

Click here for the application form for mentees (valid all year long).

Apply to be a Mentor

Click here to apply as a mentor. Applications are welcome at any time.

Eligibility Requirements

For mentees, we require applicants to be

  • Applicants must be students enrolled at an institution (For the moment, we only accept applications from students. In later rounds of ACL mentorship programs, we will open to non-student applicants.)

  • Applicants should be relatively junior in NLP (e.g., with relatively few existing publications) and lack resources (e.g., with limited NLP research guidance from local universities)

Apart from the above cases, we also encourage people to apply if they have special reasons for mentorship, and in your application form, feel free to explain your situation and why our mentorship will be important to you.

Welcome to apply here as a mentee.

________________________________

For mentors, we welcome people who are experienced in NLP and willing to share their experiences:

  • The workload will be attending the mentorship events (e.g., zoom calls to give advice to students)

  • We will match you with a group of mentees. And there will be exchange of Q&As between you and the mentees.

Welcome to apply here as a mentor.


Shall you have any questions, please feel free to check the Frequent Q&A, or contact us.

Waiting for Acceptance

While waiting for your application results, you can feel free to check our list of resources which include many tips to help solve common confusions when starting to do NLP research.

ACL Year-Round Mentorship For quiries, feel free to contact mentorship@aclweb.org
